<TITLE> Mirza Aziz calls for global action on economy, climate </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 14 (bdnews24.com) - Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam has stressed global action for combating financial turmoil and climate change in his address to the annual meeting of the World Bank-IMF being held in Washington DC The World Bank in response to the adviser's urge has assured support for a climate change action plan The Bangladesh Embassy in Washington quoted the finance adviser in a statement issued from the US Monday: "Countries most vulnerable to climate change due to their geographical locations should be given adequate grant assistance additional to normal assistance packages, to meet both adaptation and mitigation needs." The WB's assurance came after the adviser met with the bank's managing director Ngozi N Okonjo Iweala and other high level officials, the Bangladesh embassy said in a separate statement. Iweala assured Mirza Aziz that the WB would do its best to immediately activate the multi-donor trust fund for climate change and mobilise resources including those from its newly established climate investment funds. bd
